The `DotGlobeHero` component is a React component that renders a dynamic, wireframe globe background within a full-screen hero section. It utilizes `@react-three/fiber` and `@react-three/drei` for WebGL rendering.

## Key Exports

- `DotGlobeHero`: The main React component.
- `DotGlobeHeroProps`: The type definition for the props accepted by `DotGlobeHero`.

## Props

- `rotationSpeed` (optional, `number`): Controls the speed at which the globe rotates. Defaults to `0.005`.
- `globeRadius` (optional, `number`): Determines the radius of the globe. Defaults to `1`.
- `className` (optional, `string`): Allows for custom styling of the main container div using Tailwind CSS classes.
- `children` (optional, `React.ReactNode`): Content to be displayed within the hero section, overlaid on top of the globe.

## Usage Example

```jsx
import { DotGlobeHero } from '@/components/ui/globe-hero';

function MyHeroSection() {
  return (
    <DotGlobeHero rotationSpeed={0.01} globeRadius={1.5} className="text-white">
      <h1 className="text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Welcome to DocMed</h1>
      <p className="text-xl">Your documentation hub.</p>
    </DotGlobeHero>
  );
}

export default MyHeroSection;
```
